FBIS4-6279 "dreas075_c_94049" FBIS-EAS-94-075 Daily Report 17 Apr 1994 North Korea Kim Il-song Notes Zimbabwe's 14th Anniversary Kim Il-song Notes Zimbabwe's 14th Anniversary SK1704090394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0842 GMT 17 Apr 94 SK1704090394 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN [Text] Pyongyang, April 17 (KCNA) -- Comrade Kim Il-song, general secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea and president of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, on April 15 sent a message of greetings to Robert G. Mugabe, first secretary and president of the Central Committee of the Zimbabwe African National Union-Patriotic Front and president of the Republic of Zimbabwe, on the occasion of the 14th founding anniversary of the republic. In the message President Kim Il-song said he was glad of the great progress made by the Zimbabwean people in their efforts to promote national unity and develop the economy under the correct leadership of the president after the founding of the republic. He wished the president and people of Zimbabwe great success in the work for the independent development and prosperity of the country, and expressed the belief that the excellent relations of friendship and cooperation between the two countries would continue to grow stronger and develop in the future.
